",[54,72,73],{},"project-based learning model",", blending ",[54,76,77],{},"academic theory",", ",[54,80,81],{},"practical experience",", and ",[54,84,85],{},"research-oriented teaching",".",[50,88,89,90,93,94,78,97,78,100,82,103,86,106,108,109,112],{},"At UTBM, I pursued a ",[54,91,92],{},"Computer Science Engineering degree",", designed to train versatile engineers with strong foundations in ",[54,95,96],{},"programming",[54,98,99],{},"embedded systems",[54,101,102],{},"networks",[54,104,105],{},"software design",[68,107],{},"\nThe program combines rigorous scientific courses with numerous ",[54,110,111],{},"hands-on projects",", encouraging teamwork, innovation, and professional development.",[114,115],"hr",{},[45,117,119],{"id":118},"what-i-learned","What I Learned",[121,122,123,128,134,174,181,185,198,232,235,239,245,278,285,289,299,339,348,352,362,424,427,431,437,469,476,480,490,528],"steps",{},[124,125,127],"h3",{"id":126},"programming-software-engineering","Programming & Software Engineering",[50,129,130,131,133],{},"My time at UTBM strengthened my programming abilities and software design skills across multiple paradigms.",[68,132],{},"\nI developed, tested, and deployed applications using a broad set of languages and tools:",[135,136,137,144,150,156,162,168],"ul",{},[138,139,140,143],"li",{},[54,141,142],{},"C / C++"," â†’ low-level programming, performance optimization, and object-oriented design",[138,145,146,149],{},[54,147,148],{},"Java / JavaFX"," â†’ desktop applications, graphical interfaces, and advanced OOP principles",[138,151,152,155],{},[54,153,154],{},"TypeScript & JavaScript"," â†’ modern front-end development and reactive web design",[138,157,158,161],{},[54,159,160],{},"PHP"," â†’ backend logic, MVC architectures, and dynamic web applications",[138,163,164,167],{},[54,165,166],{},"Python"," â†’ scripting, prototyping, and automation",[138,169,170,173],{},[54,171,172],{},"SQL & PLpgSQL"," â†’ complex queries, data integrity, and stored procedures",[50,175,176,177,180],{},"Through these experiences, I learned to write ",[54,178,179],{},"clean, maintainable, and modular code",", while understanding the importance of architecture, testing, and documentation.",[124,182,184],{"id":183},"embedded-systems-hardware-interaction","Embedded Systems & Hardware Interaction",[50,186,187,188,190,191,193,194,197],{},"A strong emphasis was placed on ",[54,189,99],{},", where I learned to bridge software with hardware.",[68,192],{},"\nUsing ",[54,195,196],{},"STM32 microcontrollers",", I explored:",[135,199,200,205,214,219,227],{},[138,201,202],{},[54,203,204],{},"Analog and digital signal processing",[138,206,207,210,211],{},[54,208,209],{},"Timer configuration"," and ",[54,212,213],{},"interrupt management",[138,215,216],{},[54,217,218],{},"UART communication protocols",[138,220,221,210,224],{},[54,222,223],{},"Peripheral drivers",[54,225,226],{},"real-time constraints",[138,228,229],{},[54,230,231],{},"Debugging and cross-compilation toolchains",[50,233,234],{},"These projects taught me how systems operate close to the hardware layer and how to design software that interacts efficiently with electronic components.",[124,236,238],{"id":237},"networks-systems-cybersecurity","Networks, Systems & Cybersecurity",[50,240,241,242,244],{},"I gained a solid understanding of how computers communicate and how to protect data in distributed environments.",[68,243],{},"\nThis included:",[135,246,247,253,264,270],{},[138,248,249,252],{},[54,250,251],{},"Network configuration"," (routing, VLANs, and addressing)",[138,254,255,258,259,263],{},[54,256,257],{},"System administration"," with ",[260,261,262],"code",{},"Linux"," (processes, permissions, automation via Bash)",[138,265,266,269],{},[54,267,268],{},"Security fundamentals"," â€” encryption, authentication, and secure communication protocols",[138,271,272,210,275],{},[54,273,274],{},"Applied cryptography",[54,276,277],{},"blockchain principles",[50,279,280,281,284],{},"These experiences helped me understand how ",[54,282,283],{},"reliable, secure infrastructures"," are built and maintained in modern computing environments.",[124,286,288],{"id":287},"databases-information-systems","Databases & Information Systems",[50,290,291,292,295,296,298],{},"I also deepened my knowledge of ",[54,293,294],{},"data organization and management",", learning how to model, query, and optimize information systems.",[68,297],{},"\nTopics covered included:",[135,300,301,309,317,323,329],{},[138,302,303,210,306],{},[54,304,305],{},"Entityâ€“Relationship (ER) modeling",[54,307,308],{},"UML diagramming",[138,310,311,210,314],{},[54,312,313],{},"Database normalization",[54,315,316],{},"transactional integrity",[138,318,319,322],{},[54,320,321],{},"Advanced SQL"," with triggers, indexes, and views",[138,324,325,328],{},[54,326,327],{},"NoSQL databases"," (MongoDB) and data aggregation",[138,330,331,334,335,338],{},[54,332,333],{},"ETL processes"," and basic ",[54,336,337],{},"data warehousing"," concepts",[50,340,341,342,258,345,86],{},"This theoretical foundation was applied through the design of real-world web systems combining ",[54,343,344],{},"frontend interfaces",[54,346,347],{},"relational backends",[124,349,351],{"id":350},"web-development-full-stack-applications","Web Development & Full-Stack Applications",[50,353,354,355,358,359,361],{},"My formation also focused heavily on ",[54,356,357],{},"modern web development",", emphasizing clean design, scalability, and responsive interaction.",[68,360],{},"\nI practiced:",[135,363,364,376,386,402,411],{},[138,365,366,367,78,370,82,373],{},"Structuring front-end applications with ",[54,368,369],{},"HTML5",[54,371,372],{},"CSS3",[54,374,375],{},"TypeScript",[138,377,378,379,382,383],{},"Building ",[54,380,381],{},"RESTful APIs"," and handling ",[54,384,385],{},"client-server communication",[138,387,388,389,78,392,82,395,398,399],{},"Managing ",[54,390,391],{},"state",[54,393,394],{},"components",[54,396,397],{},"routing"," with frameworks such as ",[54,400,401],{},"Angular",[138,403,404,405,210,408],{},"Ensuring ",[54,406,407],{},"responsive design",[54,409,410],{},"cross-browser compatibility",[138,412,413,414,78,417,82,420,423],{},"Using ",[54,415,416],{},"Git",[54,418,419],{},"CI/CD",[54,421,422],{},"Agile workflows"," for versioning and collaboration",[50,425,426],{},"These skills allowed me to build and maintain complete web platforms â€” from backend logic to user experience.",[124,428,430],{"id":429},"mathematics-algorithms-theoretical-foundations","Mathematics, Algorithms & Theoretical Foundations",[50,432,433,434,436],{},"The engineering curriculum also provided a strong scientific background through mathematics and algorithmic theory.",[68,435],{},"\nKey areas included:",[135,438,439,445,451,457,463],{},[138,440,441,444],{},[54,442,443],{},"Linear algebra"," â†’ matrices, transformations, and eigenvalues",[138,446,447,450],{},[54,448,449],{},"Probability & statistics"," â†’ data modeling, regression, and hypothesis testing",[138,452,453,456],{},[54,454,455],{},"Discrete mathematics"," â†’ graphs, automata, and formal logic",[138,458,459,462],{},[54,460,461],{},"Information theory"," â†’ coding, entropy, and compression",[138,464,465,468],{},[54,466,467],{},"Analysis & algebra"," â†’ continuous functions and numerical methods",[50,470,471,472,475],{},"This theoretical grounding enhanced my ",[54,473,474],{},"problem-solving abilities"," and helped me understand the mathematical foundations behind algorithms and computer systems.",[124,477,479],{"id":478},"engineering-approach-team-collaboration","Engineering Approach & Team Collaboration",[50,481,482,483,486,487,489],{},"Every semester involved ",[54,484,485],{},"collaborative projects",", requiring teamwork, planning, and documentation.",[68,488],{},"\nI learned to:",[135,491,492,502,509,516],{},[138,493,494,495,210,498,501],{},"Apply ",[54,496,497],{},"Agile principles",[54,499,500],{},"SCRUM"," organization",[138,